7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Automation Anywhere and Make (Integromat) share a solid foundation of core features including Visual Builder, Code Support, Api Connections, Scheduling. Interestingly, both platforms offer nearly identical feature sets. The difference lies more in the implementation quality and depth of each feature rather than feature availability itself. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Automation Anywhere holds an overall score of 8/10 and an ease of use score of 5/10, while Make (Integromat) scores 9/10 overall and 7/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
8:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, both Automation Anywhere and Make (Integromat) offer flexible pricing models. Make (Integromat) stands out by offering a free plan, giving you a risk-free way to explore the platform. Automation Anywhere requires a paid subscription from the start."}]]}]
